OC Volume version 1.0.0 README
------------------------------

WHO are we?
-----------

OrangeCow (OC) is a non-profit organization that
devotes its resources to bring free and useful
sofware for the public. 


WHAT is OC Volume?
------------------

OC Volume is the first software released by OrangeCow
organization. The aim of this program is to enable
voice communication with computers. OC Volume is a
speech recognition engine written in Java, and should
be integrated with other applications to create
voice-driven software. 


WHEN did we start the project?
------------------------------

The OC Volume project started on March 28, 2002. 


WHY free and open-source?
-------------------------

Members of OrangeCow organization believe that things
should be free since we all enjoy free stuff. Our aim
is not to make money but to help human-to-computer
communication research field. We decide to make our
software Open-Source to better benefit programmers
and those who want to contribute. 

WHERE can I find it?
--------------------

OC Volume can be found at
http://ocvolume.sourceforge.net

HOW do I use it?
----------------

Please refer to documentation at above website.